    ```javascript
function fixedBoundSubarrays(nums, minK, maxK) {
    let count = 0, min_index = -1, max_index = -1;
    for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
        if(nums[i]===minK) min_index=i;
        else if(nums[i]===maxK) max_index=i;
        count += Math.min(min_index, max_index)+1;
    }
    return count;
}
```

    We initialize counter, min_index, and max_index variables. Iterate through the given nums array. Inside the loop, we check if the current element of nums equals minK or maxK, and we update min_index or max_index accordingly.

After updating min_index and/or max_index, we calculate the minimum of min_index and max_index, and add it to the counter. We also add 1 to this result, since we need to account for the fixed-bound subarray itself.

At the end of the loop, return the counter representing the number of fixed-bound subarrays.

